Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mansion of Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.35,0:00:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time, it housed six talented young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One woman among the six died of a heart attack inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.10,0:00:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of "Hope," people now call it the "Mansion of Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who lived alone in the mansion - Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.36,0:00:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the husband of the woman who passed away - Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.57,0:00:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was confined in one of the rooms of\Nthe mansion by someone, and died of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.25,0:00:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his final hours, Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left us a strange message.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.54,0:00:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the walls was completely painted red.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.26,0:00:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the chair painted white was facing the red wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.80,0:00:46.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the other chair, painted black, was\Nfacing the white wall on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.26,0:00:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both chairs were nailed to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.56,0:00:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sitting on the white chair when he drew his last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.55,0:00:58.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The rival of Inspector Yamato from the\NNagano Police is Morofushi Takaaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.57,0:00:59.19,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(0,0)}Morofushi Takaaki (35)\N{\fs13}Nagano Prefecture Arano Station Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.64,0:01:04.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Nicknamed "Local Detective Koumei,"\Nhe tackled this mystery along with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.12,0:01:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what on earth was the red wall supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.73,0:01:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is magic, attack the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.82,0:01:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On Saturday nights, be sure to click on Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.38,0:01:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our suspects are full of colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the second murder occurs, things are turning out unexpectedly!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.21,0:01:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.67,0:01:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.38,0:01:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.53,0:03:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring flowers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.70,0:03:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we forgot to mention it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.41,0:03:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi and Inspector Yamato...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.33,0:03:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were classmates of that Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who\Ndied in the storage room three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.29,0:03:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Classmates?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The classmate of Kobashi Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who died in\Nthis mansion's storage room three years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.09,0:03:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This inspector being the primary discoverer\Nof Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.56,0:03:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it a mere coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.98,0:03:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My motivation for approaching this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was due to it being the anniversary of her passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After placing the flowers and departing, I took\Nnotice of something under the broken window.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An abundance of painting materials had been\Nstrewn about, which did feel suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:03:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no reply after I rang the doorbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.16,0:04:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding the door unlocked, my subordinate\Nand I decided to enter the premises.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was at that time that we discovered\Nthe body confined inside this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, is it not true that the victim's fingerprints\Nwere found on the scattered painting materials?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.05,0:04:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.93,0:04:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, on the doorknob and spray can...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your subordinate's fingerprints were found.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.77,0:04:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's akin to bamboo shoots in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.32,0:04:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bamboo shoots in the know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not "in the know," but "in the snow."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.61,0:04:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's finding bamboo shoots in the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.87,0:04:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why the bamboo shoots all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bamboo shoots appear only in spring, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.70,0:04:47.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So in China, people use that metaphor to describe\Nsomething impossible or highly unachievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.13,0:04:47.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Bamboo Shoots in the Snow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.59,0:04:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how is it impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.01,0:04:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was locked inside this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.89,0:04:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, you would try to turn the doorknob\Nin an attempt to escape, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Painting a wall red with a spray can\Nshould also leave the victim's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.19,0:05:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It also doesn't look like the culprit\Nhad returned to this room yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.57,0:05:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.53,0:05:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, given that the victim's fingerprints aren't there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.24,0:05:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be a reason why they had to be eradicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.58,0:05:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, it would be best if we visited those\Nfour who resided in this mansion one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.84,0:05:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time, we'll prepare a leading question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.18,0:05:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to go, then go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.26,0:05:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my place, why don't you take that nosy\Nbrat and the girl in your car for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.48,0:05:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I finally have Sleeping Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} all to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to make good use of his intellect to solve this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There might be topics not suitable for kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, after you've visited those four and reported\Nback, bring that brat and girl to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I do doubt you'll find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get to the discussion of the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's asleep!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:36.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} left Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, the police officer from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.06,0:06:59.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(200,260)}Midorikawa Naoki (38)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.25,0:06:59.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If it's about Shuusaku's death, I've already told you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.26,0:07:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, on the doorknob of the room\Nin which Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was confined...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.06,0:07:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found your fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.06,0:07:12.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been six years since I last lived there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.90,0:07:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can fingerprints really stay that long?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.99,0:07:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, after leaving the mansion six years ago, you never went back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are those kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.46,0:07:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're accompanying me temporarily\Ndue to extenuating circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to wait in the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.63,0:07:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I have to report to Uncle Kogorou what kind of people they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, excuse me, but haven't you been on TV often?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sone Naoki" - that name ring a bell to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.48,0:07:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recognize that name!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:07:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He often acts as a corrupt official in those historical dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sone" is my mother's maiden name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I use it as my stage name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because everyone in the mansion called\Nme "Midori" this, "Midori" that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.08,0:08:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I hadn't changed it, I may have felt I couldn't\Nstand on my own feet after leaving the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.00,0:08:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, those people in the mansion did call one another by colors?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shuusaku was my childhood friend, so\Nthe two of us greeted each other by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.03,0:08:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really now, my fingerprints were on the doorknob of Aka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.91,0:08:47.80,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(210,0)\3c&H613538&}Yamabuki Shouji (39)\NFashion Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:44.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, but of course they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After all, I used to live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.16,0:08:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just called Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} "Aka," so does\Nthat mean you were called "Yamabuki"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's my surname after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.21,0:09:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} called me "Yama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.38,0:09:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, about Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what kind of person was she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.30,0:09:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Simply speaking, she was our Madonna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.35,0:09:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the six of us she was the only female, and was a beauty too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.23,0:09:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why when we heard she was\Ndating Aka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, we were all surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.57,0:09:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also why everyone moved out of that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.53,0:09:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I was one of them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:45.77,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(250,250)}Momose Takuto (37)\N{\fs13}CG Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:43.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My fingerprints were on the doorknob of Aka's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.08,0:09:47.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, don't tell me you're suspecting me\Nsimply because I lived there at one point?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.81,0:09:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't even know when I left those!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.39,0:09:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we just wished to confirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.60,0:09:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, you were called "Momo" by everyone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.23,0:10:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.53,0:10:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think some idiot even called me "Pink"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pink...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, after moving out of the mansion, you never returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.70,0:10:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I forgot to mention, but I went back once four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.58,0:10:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to deliver a game I helped create.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.96,0:10:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Game, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.21,0:10:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just an ordinary chess game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.88,0:10:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both Aka and Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} loved chess a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:46.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(300,0)}Naoki Shirou (36)\N{\fs13}Musician
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.31,0:10:45.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,On the doorknob of Aka's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:46.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You found my fingerprints!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.70,0:10:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to check with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.20,0:10:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that's just... impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I used to live there, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.25,0:11:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, I think I went back there to visit half a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.46,0:11:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I might've also touched Aka's painting tools back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.68,0:11:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, and by "Aka" I meant Akashi's nickname!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.56,0:11:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, were you called "Shiro" by the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.27,0:11:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They never greeted me by my surname.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.77,0:11:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.31,0:11:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got an appointment with my band members!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.40,0:11:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I be excused?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.74,0:11:26.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gotta bolt right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, we'll visit another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.83,0:11:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.23,0:11:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You lead them to believe their fingerprints\Nwere on the doorknob of Akashi's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.97,0:11:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And observed their reactions, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:11:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, any results?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.10,0:12:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was indeed someone strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was very antsy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.44,0:12:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And said he might've touched some painting tools\Nduring his last visit, even though we never asked!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.28,0:12:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.49,0:12:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naoki Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, when we asked him\Nquestions before, he was also acting strangely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, although we have our eyes on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have no proof against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's rest tonight, and tomorrow morning we'll ask\NNaoki Shirou to voluntarily come to the station with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.73,0:12:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.86,0:12:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You figured out who starved Akashi Shuusaku to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.45,0:12:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.53,0:12:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After thinking it over for the night, it just dawned on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:12:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could our culprit be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the one you said was weird last night - Naoki Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.83,0:13:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sitting on the white\Nchair, and in front of him was the red wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, the red color was meant to indicate himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what about the black chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.47,0:13:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Black represents the culprit, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.35,0:13:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what will you see if you sit on the black chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.77,0:13:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A white wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.98,0:13:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, he wanted to tell us the culprit is someone\Nwho's called "White" - Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.69,0:13:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry if I sound rude, but that deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.07,0:13:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ignore him, Uehara.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.99,0:13:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that in front of the apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.17,0:13:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.01,0:13:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.22,0:14:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I had this bizarre premonition so I came to\Nhave an early look, but it was already like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Red Wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.91,0:14:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer must have seen our movements\Nlast night and decided to take action first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.87,0:14:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind," is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The item in hand might not be within one's grasp."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.76,0:14:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.30,0:14:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The item in brandy might not be within one's glass?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.43,0:14:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.72,0:14:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The item in hand might not be within one's grasp."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.98,0:14:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means even if something was placed\Nin our hand, we might still lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, just as we placed the key person\Nto solving this case under our watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.78,0:15:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've carelessly allowed him to be\Nmurdered and the culprit to break free!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was a musician, Naoki Shirou, 36 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.13,0:15:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death was\Nbetween 10:00 and 11:00 last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is suffocation due to\Nconstriction on the neck - strangulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was apparently seated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.40,0:15:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And facing the chair, the closet doors have been\Nsprayed by the can next to the victim's feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.57,0:15:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing as it was painted bloody red...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.28,0:15:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly probable that the culprit is the same guy who\Nstarved the imprisoned Akashi Shuusaku a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.25,0:15:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a Red Wall again...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.21,0:15:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means, this red wall is also the victim's dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:15:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.55,0:16:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to paint the wall red...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had to do it before being strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.85,0:16:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it's equally unlikely that he would have\Npainted the wall before he met with the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, about this red wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.73,0:16:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think the culprit painted the wall red on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, isn't this weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.49,0:16:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would a culprit leave a declarative dying message like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.87,0:16:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're trying to challenge us police!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.87,0:16:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding the red wall Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left, they\Ndecided to reproduce it at this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.71,0:16:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe they are attempting to taunt us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Come solve this mystery, and catch me if you can."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.43,0:16:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we know one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.64,0:16:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspects are those who lived in\Nthe mansion with Akashi Shuusaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.77,0:16:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor Midorikawa Naoki...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.56,0:16:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fashion designer Yamabuki Shouji...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.94,0:17:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And CG creator Momose Takuto, these three people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.91,0:17:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because those three and the victim,\NNaoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, were the only ones we told...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.54,0:17:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the wall painted bloody red...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.79,0:17:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was seated on a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.50,0:17:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we didn't tell them that Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died on a chair\Npainted white, with a chair painted black behind him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.97,0:17:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor the fact that both chairs were nailed to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, even if they wanted to recreate Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death\Nscene, the culprit could only put the victim on a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't the culprit gonna worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.03,0:17:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without fully acknowledging the last death scene,\Nthey still tried to imitate the dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.29,0:17:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.45,0:17:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's best that we asked those three what they\Nwere doing between 10:00 and 11:00 last night, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.38,0:18:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still want to discuss some things with\NSleeping Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.47,0:18:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry Koumei, but I'll need to have you\Ntake the brat and girl in your car again...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Give advice and good guidance, then halt after such is of no avail...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.98,0:18:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Do not disgrace yourself for it."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.86,0:18:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kansuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, it seems your desire is to\Nhave that fine young man accompany me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.49,0:18:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But allow me to decline this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please permit me to investigate this alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, once I discover the truth, I promise I'll contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.22,0:18:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what was that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about giving advice or whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.19,0:18:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I think they're words by Confucius.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When people make a mistake, it is nice to give them advice, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they don't listen, just leave them alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise you'll do yourself a disservice by wasting\Nyour time and effort; that's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, during a past investigation,\NKan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} got caught under an avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.54,0:19:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard about him injuring his left eye,\Nleft leg, and going missing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.72,0:19:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During that time, we lost contact with Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.43,0:19:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Inspector Morofushi, despite his superior's\Norders, dashed to another prefecture alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.27,0:19:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conducted an unauthorized investigation,\Narrested the suspect Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} was after...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.44,0:19:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obtained information about the avalanche,\Nand found Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.36,0:19:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, he was punished and\Nmoved to the local police department.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} owed him one...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to prevent Inspector Morofushi from starting another rash\Ninvestigation alone, I think that's why you let this kid tag along with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.96,0:20:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is smart, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.21,0:20:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But c'mon, his rash investigation was because\Nhe wanted to find you as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's likely to recklessly go off alone again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.47,0:20:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you heard of a book called\N"Koumei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} from Second Grade Class A!"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I've read it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about a famous young student detective\Nsolving a mystery that occurred in school, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The author of that book is the one who died three years\Nago in that mansion's storage room - Kobashi Aoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was Akashi Shuusaku's wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.71,0:20:42.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the main character of the book...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That student detective is actually derived from...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Morofushi Takaaki over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.43,0:20:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there's also a rival detective\Nfrom another class who uses rough language...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.93,0:21:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.23,0:21:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably derived from Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.10,0:21:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.81,0:21:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we suppose this serial murder case is done by someone\Nwho's holding a grudge over the death of Kobashi Aoi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.57,0:21:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei would probably tackle this case without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.62,0:21:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he still cherishes that book and\Neven keeps it in his glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.67,0:21:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uehara, call a taxi and go after Koumei's car!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.51,0:21:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll check out those three guys with Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.43,0:21:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.72,0:21:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you already know, but don't let\Nyour eyes off Koumei even for a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.47,0:21:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.14,0:21:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, if you don't want him to investigate\Nrashly alone, why don't you just go with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.44,0:21:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you wanted to monitor him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.19,0:21:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even yesterday when we went with Inspector Morofushi to\Nquestion those suspects, a strange car was following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.95,0:22:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was an officer's car, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.16,0:22:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why monitor him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just told you that those three knew about\Nthe red wall at the crime scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.09,0:22:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course that information was also known to us police.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.30,0:22:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, since we know someone who was friends with Kobashi\NAoi is in the police force, shouldn't we take a closer look?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.31,0:22:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that Morofushi Takaaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.03,0:22:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's also one of the suspects!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.07,0:24:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.03,0:24:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You lost sight of Koumei!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.58,0:24:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei should be headed to the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.50,0:24:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go there now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.96,0:24:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.83,0:24:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was written in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The late... Koumei.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.63,0:24:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Mansion of Death!
